	<tr><td>
			<h3>Basic Equipment (only 8):</h3><%= image_tag "basic_equipment.jpg", :class => "home-pics2" %> 
			<br>These 8 pieces of equipment will cook most meals: 
			<ol>
				<li>A Good Knife</li>
				<li>(optional) A Knife Honer</li>
				<li>A Can Opener</li>
				<li>A Cutting Board (Two recommended if you cook meat.  Keep one for preparing meat and the other for preparing cooked items and vegetables.)</li>
				<li>A Basic Pot with Lid (Pot size depends on your family.  The pictured pot is good for 4 people </li>
				<li>A Basic Saute Pan with Lid (Pan size depends on your family.  The pictured orange saute pan is good for 4 people.</li>
				<li>A Collander</li>
				<li>A Large Mixing Bowl</li>
			</ol>
		</td>
		<td style="vertical-align: top;"><h3>Basic Spices (only 7):</h3>
		  <%= image_tag "basic_pantry.jpg", :class => "home-pics2" %>
			<br>These basic spices will give you a great start:
			<ol>
				<li>Salt</li>
				<li>Pepper</li>
				<li>Oregano (and/or leafy spices like Basil, Thyme and Parsley.) </li>
				<li>Curry Powder</li>
				<li>Soya Sauce (or Tamari for gluten-free)</li>
				<li>Balsamic Vinegar (or try other vinegar flavors too.)</li>
				<li>Olive Oil (use 'virgin' for dressings, and 'light' for cooking)</li>
			</ol>
			Optional: Save time by pre-mincing a batch of these common spices. Store them soaked in olive oil to keep them preserved for up to 4 weeks in the fridge:
			<ol>
				<li>Minced garlic</li>
